13
Subtitle
14
15 TO ALLOW A COURT TO WAIVE CERTAIN FEES
16 WHEN A JUVENILE IS ORDERED TO REGISTER
17 AS A SEX OFFENDER.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 9-27-356(k), concerning a juvenile being
22 ordered to register as a sex offender, is amended to read as follows:
23 (k) Once a juvenile is ordered to register as a sex offender, he or
24 she shall be subject to the registration requirements set forth in §§ 12-12-
25 904, 12-12-906, 12-12-908, 12-12-909, and 12-12-912, with the exception that
26 the circuit court may waive the two-hundred-fifty-dollar fee under § 12-12-
27 906.
